    "description": "An ancient place, cited: BAtlas 44 G4 Sarrastes",
    "details": "<p>The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: near Sarno. Smith (1854) refers to the Virgilian tradition that the Sarrastes are to be connected with the Sarno river and that they were the founders of Nuceria, although this may prove inconsistent with the historical and archaeological records.</p>",
